<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736695>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. Filellum antarcticum (Hartlaub, 1904): A, part of a coppinia showing gonothecal arrangement; B–C, distal part of gonothecae showing aperture (arrows). Lafoea dumosa (Fleming, 1820): D, hydrotheca and pedicel. Phialella belgicae (Hartlaub, 1904): E, hydrotheca and pedicel. Campanularia sp.: F, hydrotheca; G, distal part of pedicel, basal spherule and basal chamber with diaphragm. Antarctoscyphus elongatus (Jäderholm, 1904): H, internode with hydrotheca. Scale bar: 100 µm (B, C, G), 200 µm (A, D–F, H)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4736695/files/figure.png" .

